message.content:
Fix TypeScript errors in the AstroLab mobile app. Read each file before editing.

## 1. Fix Badge component to accept children

File: `C:\Users\User\AstroLabDiffusion\astrolab\apps\mobile\src\components\ui\Badge.tsx`

The Badge currently only accepts a `label` prop but screens pass children. Add `children` support.

In the interface, change:
```typescript
interface BadgeProps {
  label?: string;
  variant?: 'success' | 'warning' | 'error' | 'info' | 'neutral';
  compact?: boolean;
}
```

To:
```typescript
interface BadgeProps {
  label?: string;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
  variant?: 'success' | 'warning' | 'error' | 'info' | 'neutral';
  compact?: boolean;
}
```

And in the function destructuring, add `children`:
Find:
```
export function Badge({ label, variant
```
Replace to add children param.

And in the text rendering, use `{children ?? label}` instead of just `{label}`.

## 2. Fix Card.tsx — Wrapper type issue

File: `C:\Users\User\AstroLabDiffusion\astrolab\apps\mobile\src\components\ui\Card.tsx`

Read the file. The error is "JSX element type 'Wrapper' does not have any construct or call signatures." This usually happens when conditionally assigning a component type. Fix by using proper typing.

If the code does something like:
```tsx
const Wrapper = onPress ? Pressable : View;
```

Change it to use conditional rendering instead:
```tsx
if (onPress) {
  return <Pressable ...>{content}</Pressable>;
}
return <View ...>{content}</View>;
```

Or cast the Wrapper: `const Wrapper = (onPress ? Pressable : View) as React.ElementType;`

## 3. Fix onesignal.ts — implicit any types

File: `C:\Users\User\AstroLabDiffusion\astrolab\apps\mobile\src\lib\onesignal.ts`

Add type annotations to the event callbacks that have implicit `any`. Read the file and add `: any` to the event parameters on lines that have errors (around line 11 and 15).

Read all files before editing!

